          "science": "This is about emotional regulation and avoiding 'amygdala hijack' (a term from Daniel Goleman's work on emotional intelligence) — when we feel threatened, the thinking brain goes offline and the reactive brain takes over. Pausing, slowing your breathing and lowering your voice are proven ways to keep the rational brain in charge.",
