          "mins": 6,
          "body": "Here's the thing most owners learn the hard way: pay matters right up until it's fair, and then it goes quiet. A bloke on a fair rate who's bored, ignored and micromanaged will still walk — and a few grand won't stop him. A bloke who's a bit underpaid but trusted, learning, and proud of the work will often stay for years.\n\nThat's not soft talk. Underpay someone and you've got a problem. But once the money's sorted, throwing more at a flat, unhappy worker is like topping up a tank that isn't leaking. The leak is somewhere else.\n\nSo the question stops being 'are we paying enough?' and becomes 'is the work itself any good to do?' That's where the next three lessons come in — the three things that, once pay is fair, actually keep a good lab tech or field hand engaged.",
